FBIS3-41257 "jptdd007__l94047" JPRS-TDD-94-007-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Narcotics 14 February 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA EGYPT Authorities Seize 20 Kg of Heroin in Aswan NC0702195594 Cairo AL-AHRAM in Arabic 5 Feb 94 p 1 NC0702195594 Cairo AL-AHRAM Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] After three months of extensive searching, the various departments of the general administration for narcotics, in cooperation with security officers from Bani Suwayf and al-Minya, succeeded in seizing 20 kilograms of heroin amounting to 25 million pounds. An Egyptian belonging to the international mafia gangs was trying to smuggle the heroin to flood the governorates with the white poison. The car is a public sector car registered to an iron-casting company in Aswan. The operation to seize the vehicle took place after tracking and pursuing them for over 750 kilometers starting from Idfu in Aswan up to Cairo.
